message.content: cs.IT, cs.IT is the most likely category as the paper deals with channel coding and information theory. Other likely categories could be cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) as the paper mentions the asymptotic equipartition property, which is a fundamental concept in information theory and data compression. cs.CC (computational complexity) could also be a likely category as the paper discusses the complexity of estimating regular functions of channel outputs. cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) and cs.LG (machine learning) could also be possible categories as the paper mentions the use of concentration of measure property and related methods to estimate functions and quadratic forms.
